# Postfix transport map for DarkPipe cloud relay
#
# ROUTING LOGIC:
# - Mail destined for user domains (listed below) is forwarded to the Go relay
#   daemon on localhost:10025. The daemon then tunnels it via WireGuard/mTLS
#   to the home device for final delivery.
# - Mail destined for ALL OTHER domains (external recipients) is delivered via
#   normal internet SMTP (Postfix default transport). This handles outbound
#   mail from the home device that was relayed here for delivery.
#
# IMPORTANT: Do NOT use a wildcard (* smtp:[127.0.0.1]:10025) here.
# A wildcard would route outbound mail from the home device back to the relay
# daemon, creating a routing loop: home -> cloud relay -> relay daemon -> home.
#
# To add additional user domains, add one line per domain using the same pattern.
#
# This file is hashed with `postmap lmdb:/etc/postfix/transport` in the
# entrypoint script to create transport.lmdb.

# User domains -> relay daemon -> WireGuard tunnel -> home device
${RELAY_DOMAIN} smtp:[127.0.0.1]:10025
